Description: Egypt, view of entrance arch of ruined temple complex at Karnak. Relief carvings, including depictions of figures, on arch. Medium group of adult males walking and standing below arch. One male wearing military-uniform, others wearing gowns, head-gear. Medium: Gelatin silver print.
Producer name: Photographed by: John Frederick Clifford Hunt
Curator's comments: Structure is a pylon [entrance]. J M Hudson, 27/01/1998. Circumstances: The Imperial War Museum holds photographs from the same collection with a more military content - see [HUN-] PIC DOC 66.
